(41, 11, 9, 42, 19, 37, 38, 'Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord', 'Praise for the Coming King', 'Both passages emphasize the acclamation of Jesus as the one who comes in the name of the Lord. The phrase ''Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord'' in Mark parallels ''Blessed be the King that cometh in the name of the Lord'' in Luke, highlighting a shared theme of recognition and celebration.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 11, 9, 43, 12, 13, 13, 'Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord', 'Connection of Hosanna and Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize the cry of ''Hosanna'' and the blessing for one who comes in the name of the Lord. This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as a significant figure during his entry into Jerusalem.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 11, 9, 43, 19, 15, 15, 'Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord', 'Contrast of Acclamation and Rejection', 'This connection highlights the shift from the crowd''s joyful acclamation of Jesus as king in Mark 11:9 to their vehement rejection and demand for his crucifixion in John 19:15. Both passages emphasize the contrasting responses to Jesus'' kingship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 11, 10, 26, 37, 24, 25, 'kingdom of our father David', 'Connection of David''s Kingship', 'This connection highlights the theme of David''s kingship in both passages. Mark 11:10 references the kingdom of David, while Ezekiel 37:24-25 speaks of David as a king over the people, emphasizing the continuity of Davidic leadership.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 11, 10, 42, 2, 14, 14, 'in the highest', 'Connection of Praise and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize a call for divine recognition and exaltation. ''In the highest'' in both verses highlights a shared theme of glorifying God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
